===Noun===

{{en-noun}}

# With respect to [[television]] programming, commercial or otherwise, the content of a show can be broken into segments of several minutes. Typically, additional content is inserted between the segments, and (typically) the additional content consists of advertisements. The advertising content "wraps around" the actual show content. Advertising content is not the only possible type of wraparound content, and some shows feature hosts or hostesses (as well as advertisements) between the show segments. These hosts are referred to as wraparound hosts, and they may provide commentary on the show, perform skits, ask for money for a charitable cause, etc. Well known examples of wraparound hostesses are [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vampira Vampira] and [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elvira Elvira, Mistress of the Dark], who are well known in the United States for commenting on horror movies between scenes.



